                <h1>How to Make Background Transparent in Photoshop</h1>
                <p>To make a background transparent in Photoshop, select the layer with the image. Use the Magic Wand Tool or Quick Selection Tool to outline the area you want to remove. Press Delete to erase it, making the background transparent. You can refine the edges with the Eraser Tool or Layer Masks for a smoother look. Finally, save as PNG to preserve transparency.</p>
